<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8480> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8480" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 735, footnote 97" ;
	dprr:hasID 8480 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7219> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7219" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 166. The connection with Spain implied in his appointment in 171 to the commission on misgovernment there (Liv. 43.2.5, 7; MRR 1.419) may well have been made after 191, the date suggested by Münzer; cf. MRR 1.355. See Sumner, Orators 37-38, who also suggests that he was, like his fellow envoy, L. Aurelius Cotta, a military tribune under Aemilius Paullus in Liguria in 182-181 (Liv. 42.27.6, and 28.8) and would change the praenomen L. in that passage to C. It would be the only example of L. among the patrician Sulpicii." ;
	dprr:hasID 7219 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2827> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2827" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to observe conditions in Greece, to arbitrate a territorial dispute between Sparta and Megalopolis, and particularly to inves{440}tigate the actions of Eumenes of Pergamum and Antiochus of Syria, even hearing accusations against Eumenes publicly at Sardis (Polyb. 31.1.6-8, and 6.1-6; Diod. 31.7.2; Pausan. 7.11.1-3; cf. SIG\n     665, line 44)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2827 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2807> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2807" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Rep. 1.21 and 23; Liv. 45.44.2; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 50f., 123, 460f.; Plin. NH 2.53; Suet. Vit. Ter. 4; Obseq. 12; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; cf. Didasc. Ter. And. (Donatus). Claudius served against the Alpine Gauls and Sulpicius against the Ligurians, and both celebrated triumphs (Liv. Per. 46; Act. Tr. Cap. and Urbisalv., Degrassi 80f., 338f., 556f.)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2807 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2789> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2789" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Had command of the winter camp; and was rebuked by Paullus for guarding Perseus carelessly and indulging his soldiers (Liv. 45.27.6, and 28.10; see 168, Legates)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2789 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2785> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2785" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably all or almost all the Tribunes of the Soldiers and the Lieutenants who served in Macedonia and Illyria continued until their respective commanders returned." ;
	dprr:hasID 2785 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2767> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2767" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, Tribunes of the Soldiers." ;
	dprr:hasID 2767 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2749> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2749" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Paullus at Pydna, where he forewarned the soldiers of a lunar eclipse (Polyb. 29.16.1; Cic. Rep. 1.23, legatus; Liv. 44.37.5-9; Val. Max. 8.11.1, legatus; Plin. NH 2.53; Quintil. Inst. Or. 1.10.47; Frontin. Str. 1.12.8; Plut. Aem. 17.5-7)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2749 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2706> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2706" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Aided the levy (Liv. 43.14.2-5, 15.1 and 4-5), and provided winter supplies for the army in Macedonia (44.16.4); put on the Thyestes of Ennius (Cic. Brut. 78). Cf. Liv. 43.16.11; 44.17.3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2706 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2700> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2700" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 43.11.7 Provinces and armies Liv. 43.11.8, 12.1-11, 15.2-3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2700 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2667> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2667" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A commission, apparently of former officials in Spain, chosen as patrons by peoples of Spain who complained of the peculations of the following governors: 1. M. Titinius (Curvus) (see 178, 177, 176), who was acquitted; 2. P. Furius Philus (see 174, 173, 172); and 3. C. (not M.) Matienus (see 173), who both went into exile (Liv. 43.2.1-11). On Cato, see D.- G. 5.130, no. 15." ;
	dprr:hasID 2667 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2426> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2426" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Aemilius Paullus to the Senate (Liv. 40.28.8)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2426 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2406> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2406" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably Legates of Paullus throughout his command in Liguria (Liv. 40.28.8; see 181, Legates; and Münzer, RE no. 66)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2406 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2195> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2195" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 43.2.1-11, on which Münzer (RE) bases the conjecture that he served under Aemilius Paullus in Spain." ;
	dprr:hasID 2195 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10327> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10327" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/26> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A.97" ;
	dprr:hasID 10327 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10224> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10224" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Liguribus Tal[...]rneis. MRR I.437, Itgenshorst no. 204, Rich no. 203." ;
	dprr:hasID 10224 .
